            "width": 2635,
            "height": 3000,
            "alt_text": "A print features at its center a version of Pablo Picasso's \"The Old Guitarist\"—depicting, in various shades of blue, an old man sitting cross-legged, playing guitar. Around it are smaller sketches related to Picasso's work in red and blue. At the top, \"Pablo Picasso Spanish 1881\" is written in red type, at the bottom \"The Old Guitarist 1903.\""
